One of the principal reasons why a general proof regarding the existence or otherwise of equilibria in the Parker problem remains so challenging arises from the need to precisely specify and maintain the magnetic field topology while solving the force-free equations (see, e.g., Low 2010b). Indeed, Parker (1986) argued that the requirement to simultaneously satisfy J×B=0\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
