				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\gamma $$\end{document} is a scaling factor that can be absorbed into the artificial time of the evolution. The integrated forces within the domain are then reduced until they fall below some chosen threshold. Craig and Sneyd (1986) argue that the stability properties of the resulting (numerical) equilibrium are not affected by the fictitious evolution.

