A substantial body of work addressing the Parker problem in the RMHD framework has focussed on the turbulent nature of the statistically steady state. The first such studies were performed by Einaudi et al. (1996) and Dmitruk and Gómez (1997). They in fact solved a 2D problem, replacing the ∂/∂z\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
